What happens when you type https://www.google.com
 in your browser and press Enter

When you type https://www.google.com
 in your browser and press Enter, several processes happen behind the scenes:

DNS request is made to convert the domain name into an IP address.
TCP/IP connection is established using a 3-way handshake.
Firewall checks and filters the request for security.
HTTPS/SSL handshake encrypts the connection.
Load balancer distributes the request to available servers.
Web server receives the request and processes it.
Application server runs backend logic and prepares data.
Database is queried if data is needed.
Response is sent back to the browser.
Browser renders the page (HTML, CSS, JavaScript).
